HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 250
BY REPRESENTATIVE MUSCARELLO
A RESOLUTION
To commend the Tangipahoa Parish Sheriff's Office Mounted Division on its service to the
parish and to recognize the 2025 Tangipahoa Parish Sheriff's Office Mounted
Division Rodeo Queens.
WHEREAS, the Tangipahoa Parish Sheriff's Office (TPSO) Mounted Division is a
volunteer organization that consists of deputies who offer their time, vehicles, horse trailers,
and trained horses to serve Tangipahoa Parish and the surrounding area; and
WHEREAS, the TPSO Mounted Division volunteer deputies and their equine
partners serve year-round, assisting with rescue and recovery operations, providing security
at high school athletic events and parish fairs and festivals, and hosting the TPSO Mounted
Division Rodeo every September; and
WHEREAS, the TPSO Mounted Division Rodeo was established in 2011 as a
fundraiser to help volunteer deputies fund bullet-proof vests, horse tack and equipment, and
other costs associated with serving the parish; and
WHEREAS, the TPSO Mounted Division Rodeo is a Cajun Rodeo Association-
sanctioned rodeo event, and it has been awarded "Rodeo of the Year" four times; and
WHEREAS, the TPSO Mounted Division Rodeo will see over three thousand
spectators, in addition to its participants, over the course of the two-day rodeo; and
WHEREAS, the TPSO Mounted Division Rodeo Pageant began in 2016, and the
director of the pageant is Rebecca Borras; the pageant features five age divisions: Miss
Queen, Teen Miss Queen, Deb Miss Queen, Little Miss Queen, and Petite Miss Queen; and
WHEREAS, the 2025 Tangipahoa Parish Sheriff's Office Mounted Division Rodeo
Pageant Queens are Miss Queen Lainey Mitchell, Teen Miss Queen Kaylee Sundo, Deb
Miss Queen Madelyn Ard, Little Miss Queen Loralai McIntyre, and Petite Miss Queen
Annaleigh Cernich.
